# Azure Deployment Plan for credit-risk-api Project
## Goal
Deploy the project to Azure using AZD with two services:
- FastAPI backend API
- Streamlit dashboard frontend

## Project Information
- App Name: credit-risk-api
- Stack: Python (FastAPI, Streamlit, XGBoost/SHAP model artifacts)
- Type: ML scoring API + dashboard UI
- Containerization: Dockerfile exists at ./Dockerfile (API)
- Dependencies: HTTP dependency from dashboard to API
- Hosting: Azure Container Apps (API) + Azure App Service (Dashboard)

## Azure Resources Architecture
> Install the mermaid extension in IDE to view the architecture.
```mermaid
graph TD
svc_api["Name: credit-risk-api\nPath: .\nLanguage: python"]
svc_dash["Name: credit-risk-dashboard\nPath: dashboard\nLanguage: python"]

subgraph Compute
  subgraph acaEnv["Azure Container Apps Environment"]
    apiHost["credit-risk-api (Azure Container App)"]
  end
  dashHost["credit-risk-dashboard (Azure App Service)"]
end

svc_api -->|hosted on| apiHost
svc_dash -->|hosted on| dashHost
dashHost -.->|http| apiHost
```

- Dashboard sends HTTP scoring requests to API.
- API is stateless and serves model artifacts from packaged files in the app image.

## Recommended Azure Resources
Application credit-risk-api:
- Hosting Service Type: Azure Container Apps
- SKU: Consumption (serverless scale, scale-to-zero, burst traffic handling)
- Configuration:
  - language: python
  - Environment Variables: []
  - dockerFilePath: ./Dockerfile
  - dockerContext: ./
- Dependencies Resource: none required

Application credit-risk-dashboard:
- Hosting Service Type: Azure App Service (Linux)
- SKU: B1 Basic (single instance for low-to-medium traffic, always-on process)
- Configuration:
  - language: python
  - Environment Variables:
    - API_URL (set to deployed API base URL)
    - PORT (platform-provided)
  - dockerFilePath: n/a (source-based deploy)
  - dockerContext: n/a
- Dependencies Resource:
  - Dependency Name: credit-risk-api
  - SKU: ACA Consumption
  - Service Type: Azure Container Apps
  - Connection Type: http
  - Environment Variables: [API_URL]

## Recommended Supporting Services
- Application Insights
- User-Assigned Managed Identity
- Log Analytics Workspace
- Container Registry

## Recommended Security Configurations
- Assign User-Assigned Managed Identity to supported resources.
- Grant AcrPull role to the managed identity on ACR.
- Restrict CORS origins in production for API.

## Execution Step
> Below are the steps for Copilot to follow; ask Copilot to update or execute this plan.
> CRITICAL: Do NOT run az login until Env setup step.

Execution Steps:
1. Containerization
- [x] Dockerfile found: ./Dockerfile
- [ ] Create dashboard Dockerfile only if moving dashboard to container hosting (optional path).
- [ ] Build/push image(s) to ACR during azd deploy.

2. Create Azure Infrastructure Files for AZD (no Azure login in this step)
- [ ] Provisioning tool: AZD
- [ ] Expected files: azure.yaml, infra/main.bicep, infra/main.parameters.json
- [ ] If files are missing, generate them based on plan.
- [ ] Validate generated IaC and fix errors.

3. Env setup for AZD
- [ ] Install Azure CLI and AZD if missing.
- [ ] Run: azd env new crisk-dev --no-prompt
- [ ] Set required env values (subscription, location, service settings, API_URL wiring).
- [ ] Set subscription and resource group variables.

4. Deployment
- [ ] Run: azd provision --preview --no-prompt
- [ ] Run: azd up --no-prompt
- [ ] Validate API and dashboard endpoints and review logs.

5. Summarize Result
- [ ] Generate .azure/summary.copilotmd

## Progress Tracking
Copilot should update .azure/progress.copilotmd after each step with:
- Completed tasks
- Pending tasks
- Failed tasks and retry notes

